12. Qc1
{ The initial response to Be4 was to go  12.Qd1  until someone realized: why not keep the Queen on the c-file, thereby preventing c5? }
12... h6 13. Bxf6 Bxf6 14. Rd1
{ The common place for the Rook in these variations. The Rook defends the central d4-pawn, while e4 is usually adequately protected by the Knight on c3 and the Bishop on g2. }
