{ A popular position and another way to play the Catalan Benoni as Black.   Instead of choosing to fight for the e4-square after Re8, Black instead chooses to focus on the control over the e5-square and try to get b5 in quicker after Rb8. }
11. Bf4
{ The most natural move in this position, attacking d6 and taking control over e5. }
11... Qe7
{ The Queen on e7 takes direct control over e5 and in some cases the e4-square as well. This can make a difference in a few concrete lines. }
