3... a6
{ A generally useful move in the QGA which can also transpose to the mainline if Black plays  ...Nf6  and  ...c5  . However, Black can also respond with  4.e3  b5  which goes into a popular sub variation.   Apart from the variation after  3...Nf6  4.e3  Bg4  , this variation is also considered to be one of the annoying sidelines against QGA. }
