8. a3 Be7 9. cxd5 exd5 10. b4
{ In the pawn structure which exists at present, one of Black's main ideas is to execute ...c5. So White must play immediately against it. }
10... a5 11. b5 c6 12. Qa4
{ A lot of games have continued with  12.bxc6  which is also an equally good option leading to the same pawn structure.  However, a lot of games have been played there and given two equally good options, it is usually better to choose the one less travelled, as the opponent is less likely to be familiar here. Qa4 is a completely new move - a novelty. }
12... cxb5 13. Qxb5 Ba6 { The critical line. } 14. Qb2
{ The b2-square is the precise spot for the Queen. The d4- and e5-squares are very important from the point of view of strategic control in this position. As such, the White Queen always goes to b2. }
