3... d5 4. Bg2
{ I suggest this move over  4.Nf3  for a couple of reasons.   Firstly, in the event of  4...dxc4  , White has the additional option of  5.Qa4+  which is an important extra option to have.  Apart from that, in this repertoire, we choose to go Nd2 for the variations with ...Bb4+. In this case, with the Bishop on g2, Black usually doesn't have the additional option of ...dxc4 as White has Qa4+.   Black's play can be broadly divided into two avenues. One is where he takes  4...dxc4  . This leads to more open positions, where White is usually a pawn down but gets compensation by way of piece activity.  The variations apart from  4...dxc4  tend to be more closed by nature. }
4... dxc4
{ Amongst the first games in this position was the game Alekhine - Euwe, from their World Championship match in 1937.  The lines with  4...dxc4  is a popular choice as it leads to open positions, which many people find easier to play compared to the closed positions arising after  4...Be7  and  4...Bb4+  . }
5. Nf3
{ 5.Qa4+  is another option and a very natural move, which was also Alekhine's reply to Euwe. It is a reasonable move and one of the advantages of going with this 4.Bg2 move order is to retain the flexibility of this additional option.  However, we are not considering this in our repertoire, because I feel that it is a bit too simplistic and with the best play, ends up in drawish positions.  This is the starting position and Black has many different options here. }
5... Bb4+
{ This is a variation that did not enjoy a high reputation back in the times. Historically there aren't too many strong players who played this variation with Black and the initial games are filled with wins for White.   However, the variation became much more popular after 2000. Top players like Kramnik, Topalov employed this line and soon many top players started to play this. The variation is often used as an aggressive weapon by Black, with an intention to get a fighting position.   Although I have played this with Black myself, I don't have a high opinion of this variation as Black. I feel that if White knows his stuff, White can get nice positions. }
