{ The Queen's Gambit accepted is an opening that stretches back all the way. Searching through the Mega Database, there are quite a few games of Greco - NN and Philidor.   The variation was extensively discussed in the 1834 match between De Labourdonnais - McDonnell. The reputation of the opening has varied over time, but it has always had a solid reputation, and that is also the case at present.   In the recent past, it has been used with reasonable frequency by several world champions and legends like Karpov, Anand, Kasparov, and was also Fischer's choice in his return match against Spassky in 1992.   In the present times, it is played by several elite players with reasonable regularity. Caruana used this with solid effect for some of his games, and the variation is also frequently played by Alekseenko, Harikrishna among many others at the elite. }
