{ There have been four correspondence games here, out of which White has won two and drawn two.   Although the engine may not give a high evaluation of this position initially, a score of 3/4 in high-level Correspondence Chess stands some testimony to how this position is more comfortable for White. I think in practical OTB Chess this position is much more pleasant for White.   Some of the common strategic themes White can get is the opening of d-file with Ne4, Ndc5 and after Black takes ...Nxc5 at one point, dxc5.   Typical Catalan ideas on the Kingside involving the advance of the h-pawn is also quite common. }
