{ 4...Bb4+  is one of the most solid systems against the Catalan. This motif of Bb4+ before bringing back the Bishop to e7 is a typical strategic operation Black does in a few 1.d4-lines.  The idea of luring the Bishop to d2 is multi-fold. It feels a bit paradoxical that the White Bishop is placed worse at d2 compared to c1. For starters, it takes away the d2 spot from the b1-Knight. The d2-Bishop impedes Queen's vision of d4. Although this isn't often relevant, it does make a difference in some rare variations.  It is also common for White to go b3, a4 in many lines in this Catalan pawn structure in which case, the Bishop on c1 has the additional options to go to b2 and a3 apart from the usual f4. }
