16. Be3
{ A prophylactic move that moves away from any direct attacks coming from ...g5. White also prepares f4. }
16... h4 17. g4 g5 18. Rf1
{ White's next move is set to be f4 which will ensure that Black doesn't have a bind on the dark squares. At the moment, White's fixture of pawns on the light squares seems unfortunate. However, these are not permanent fixtures and White has the room to open up his pawns with moves like f4 and e5.   Black has made some strategic moves in order to try and secure the dark squares. However, this has also weakened the light squares in Black's position.   White has a light square Bishop and Black doesn't, so if White gets into a situation where he can sacrifice something like e5 and play something like Qf5 and Be4, then Black won't be able to ward off those threats easily. e5 is a popular and attractive possibility to make a strategic sacrifice in this position. }
